    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="Northwest:Tuesday saw the first Covid-19 death in the northwest when an 80-year-old woman with kidney problems died at a hospital. There were no new positive cases reported in the northwest in the period from August 14-17, though the number of confirmed cases was up to 54 by August 18. Local authorities continue to struggle to trace and test all known contacts of the infected: Of 656 contacts of known cases, just 371 have been tested (out of a total of 4,605 tests conducted in the region thus far). Two cases in Bab al-Salam IDP camp have now recovered, though measures remain in place to prevent further spread in the highly vulnerable area."/>
